  EPiSODE iNFO 
                                                        
                                                                        
  All the action from the semi-final second-leg encounter at Villa      
  Park, where the visitors begin the match with a two-goal advantage,   
  having won 3-1 in the first leg at Valley Parade. The Bantams are     
  aiming to become only the second team from the fourth tier of         
  English football to reach this final and the first since Rochdale     
  finished as runners-up in 1962. However, the Villans will be          
  determined to maintain their chances of winning silverware after a    
  disappointing campaign so far in the Premier League, and will be      
  eager to avoid a humiliating exit.                                    
                                                                        
  Notes: Pre match and post match player and manager interviews         
  included.                                                             
                                                                        
  Enjoy!
